# Plugin Development

## Plugin Crate Structure

Every downloadable plugin lives in crates/plugins/<name>/ and must:

- Set crate-type = ["cdylib"] in Cargo.toml
- Export three #[plugin_fn] functions: appz_plugin_handshake, appz_plugin_info, appz_plugin_execute
- Depend on appz_pdk for types and extism-pdk for the plugin runtime

```toml
# Example Cargo.toml
[lib]
crate-type = ["cdylib"]

[dependencies]
appz_pdk = { path = "../../appz_pdk" }
extism-pdk = "1.4.0"
serde = { workspace = true, features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1.0"
```

## Host Function Declaration

Plugins declare host functions in their lib.rs using the #[host_fn] macro:

```rust
#[host_fn]
extern "ExtismHost" {
    fn appz_pfs_read_file(input: Json<PluginFsReadInput>) -> Json<PluginFsReadOutput>;
    // ...
}
```

The generated functions return Result<Json<T>, extism_pdk::Error> -- always handle the Result before accessing .0 on the Json wrapper.

## Security Handshake

Every plugin must implement the HMAC handshake:

```rust
#[plugin_fn]
pub fn appz_plugin_handshake(
    input: Json<PluginHandshakeChallenge>,
) -> FnResult<Json<PluginHandshakeResponse>> {
    let response = appz_pdk::security::compute_handshake(&input.0);
    Ok(Json(response))
}
```

## Feature Flag Conventions

- Host functions for plugin-only features (check, site) use stubs when the feature is disabled
- Stubs live in crates/app/src/wasm/host_functions/stubs.rs
- Self-contained plugins (like ssg-migrator) do NOT need feature flags or stubs -- they use only the generic appz_pfs_* / appz_pgit_* host functions

## PDK Types

All shared types between host and plugin are in crates/appz_pdk/src/types.rs. When adding a new host function:
1. Define Input/Output structs in appz_pdk/src/types.rs
2. Re-export them from appz_pdk::prelude
3. Use the same types on both the host side (crates/app/src/wasm/types.rs) and plugin side

## Testing

```bash
# Type-check plugin for WASM
cargo check -p <plugin>-plugin --target wasm32-wasip1

# Build the WASM binary
cargo build -p <plugin>-plugin --target wasm32-wasip1 --release

# Dev override (skip CDN download)
APPZ_DEV_PLUGIN_MIGRATE=target/wasm32-wasip1/debug/ssg_migrator_plugin.wasm appz migrate .
```

## Common Mistakes

- Forgetting to handle the Result from unsafe host_fn_call(input) -- host functions return Result<Json<T>, Error>, not Json<T> directly
- Using std::fs in a plugin crate -- use the Vfs trait or host functions instead
- Including C-binding dependencies (like ast-grep) in WASM builds -- gate them behind #[cfg(feature = "native")]
- Forgetting to register a new host function in register_plugin_host_functions() in plugin.rs
